        &lt;version&gt;6.0.9.Final&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

the `javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank`is part of [Bean Validation 2.0][1] and validator for it is not present in 5.3 series.


  [1]: https://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/stable/beanvalidation/api/javax/validation/constraints/NotBlank.html

as [baeldung.com say][1] Per the JSR 380 specification, the validation-api dependency contains the standard validation APIs:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;javax.validation&lt;/groupId&gt;
       &lt;artifactId&gt;validation-api&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;2.0.0.Final&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
Hibernate Validator is the reference implementation of the validation API.
To use it, we must add the following dependencies:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
       &lt;groupId&gt;org.hibernate.validator&lt;/groupId&gt;
       &lt;artifactId&gt;hibernate-validator&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;6.0.2.Final&lt;/version&gt;
